  "texts": [
    "This approach allowed us to systematically generate nonsensical statements.",
    "• Manual Check: The generated statements were then manually reviewed to ensure quality, yielding a set of 578 validated nonsensical statements.",
    "Three graduate students specializing in computer science served as annotators and performed a cross-check of the generated nonsensical statements.",
    "Each statement had to be independently reviewed by all three annotators, and only when all agreed that a statement appropriately contradicted commonsense and was grammatically correct, it was accepted.For each nonsensical statement, we identified the corresponding explanation from the ECQA dataset, pairing them to form a complete data entry.",
    "The final CSE dataset consists of 578 nonsensical statements with corresponding explanations, providing a valuable resource for evaluating AI systems' commonsense reasoning and explanation capabilities."
  ],
